---
---

<section data-test="comparison-section" class="py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800/30">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
        Before and after
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        The same product requirement, two ways. One stays coherent under change.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- Without spec -->
      <div data-test="comparison-without" class="rounded-xl border-2 border-red-200 dark:border-red-900 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/30 px-6 py-4 border-b border-red-200 dark:border-red-800">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-red-500 font-bold text-lg">✗</span>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-red-900 dark:text-red-200">Without RootSpec</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mt-1">Vague requirements, ambiguous stories, untraceable decisions</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 p-6 font-mono text-sm">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="text-slate-400 text-xs mb-1">📄 spec.docx</div>
            <div class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded p-3 text-xs leading-relaxed">
              <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold mb-2"># Reading Tracker App</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500">Users should be able to track their books.</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-1">Make it look nice. Should work on mobile.</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-1">Add social features maybe?</p>
              <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2 italic text-xs">Last updated: 3 months ago</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="text-slate-400 text-xs mb-1">🗂️ Jira ticket BOOK-47</div>
            <div class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded p-3 text-xs">
              <p class="text-yellow-600 dark:text-yellow-400 font-medium">Story: "Add book logging"</p>
              <p class="text-slate-500 mt-1">As a user I want to log books</p>
              <p class="text-slate-400 mt-1 italic">Acceptance criteria: (none)</p>
              <p class="text-slate-400 italic">Points: 13 (??)</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/20 rounded border border-red-200 dark:border-red-800 text-xs">
            <p class="text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">⚠ What counts as "logged"? Does mobile mean native app? Social is in scope or not? AI interprets freely.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- With RootSpec -->
      <div data-test="comparison-with" class="rounded-xl border-2 border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 overflow-hidden">
        <div class="bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/30 px-6 py-4 border-b border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-emerald-500 font-bold text-lg">✓</span>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900 dark:text-emerald-200">With RootSpec</h3>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-emerald-700 dark:text-emerald-300 mt-1">Structured hierarchy, traceable decisions, testable stories</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-900 p-6 font-mono text-sm">
          <div class="mb-3 text-xs">
            <span class="text-brand-500 font-semibold">L1: Philosophy</span>
            <div class="mt-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded p-2">
              Mission: Help readers build lasting habits through <span class="text-brand-400">frictionless reflection</span>.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-3 text-xs">
            <span class="text-violet-500 font-semibold">L2: Truths</span>
            <div class="mt-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded p-2">
              Trade-off: Depth over breadth. No social features in v1 — violates focus pillar.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-3 text-xs">
            <span class="text-emerald-500 font-semibold">L5: Story US-47</span>
            <div class="mt-1 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded p-2">
              <p>Given I finish a book</p>
              <p>When I tap "Log it"</p>
              <p>Then I see a reflection prompt within 500ms</p>
              <p class="text-emerald-400">→ Traces to: frictionless reflection pillar</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-3 p-2 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-900/20 rounded border border-emerald-200 dark:border-emerald-800 text-xs">
            <p class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">✓ Every story traces to a design pillar. "Social features" rejected by L2 trade-off.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
